node.text:
In celebration of 100 years, we're introducing three new, totally reimagined #IndianChief models. Combining iconic, American V-twin style with modern performance and technology, we've designed the new Chief with a simplistic and mechanical aesthetic that pays homage to the glory days of American motorcycling. 

All based on a timeless, simplistic steel-tube frame and powered by the legendary Thunderstroke motor, the new #IndianChief, Indian #ChiefBobber and Indian #SuperChief offer three unique takes on the classic American V-twin.

#indianmotorcycle

node.text: Man, this was such a fun time in FMX and in life!!! I was 23 yrs old chasing the SX and fmx dream. @foxpetefox green lit one of the most insane, over budget, and debaucherous cult films ever made in MX. We had so much fun making this movie. I remember when we were shooting @sethenslow11 opening chase scene, we were in Vegas. We had built this massive 200 foot canyon double called “leap of fate”. Seth only got a couple jumps in cause he banged himself up on the jump while filming. Troy, who was filming/creator of the movie, asked if I would jump it w/ a helmet cam. They wanted an “on board” angle. Keep in mind, this was 1997 and there were no Gopros. They strapped a film camera to the top of a street helmet. It was like riding w/ a 30 lbs. blender strapped to your head. I hit it once and compressed the shit out of my neck. He said, “all good, we just need the one shot”. After watching the movie at the premier, I ask troy where the POV shot was? He said, “sorry dude, I forgot to put film in the camera”. Hey @foxmoto think it’s time for a remaster of this film!!!

node.text: Feels like a lifetime ago when things were “normal”. We had a chance to catch up right before the Covid lockdown. I had a great time showing them around my shop, mx track, and some of my favorite back roads In central coast, California. Can’t wait to see the magazine drop!

node.title: Thanks a ton @easyriders for coming and spending the day w/ me.

node.text: With the current climate around the world, @feedbigb and I decided to do a 4 day “Covid safe” motorcycle road trip. Big b, myself, and @johnnylaneyphoto our photog/videog all took Covid tests; and after getting a negative result we hit the road! We packed our bikes w/ camping gear and set on an adventure. We camped in camp grounds, and ate food on the curb. Was really nice to get back to basics. Here is a short video of our 1300 mile trip. Let me know what you think!! Special thanks to the sponsors that support us and @goodride charity.  @indianmotorcycle @dragspecialties @foxmoto @bell_powersports @cardosystems @wienerschnitzel @blackriflecoffee @fox  Music by: @felonsclub

node.text: @sturgisrally Pack post #2. On any big road trip these products are ALWAYS packed in one of my saddle bags. I fit all of these into one bag so that nothings is disrupted unless I need it. Here is the list. Rain gear, @thorogood_usa rain boot covers, @foxracing cold weather gloves, zip lock of rubber gloves in case of rain, @boxousadirect tool roll, satellite phone, @sigsaueracademy pistol w/ carbon holster, 2 logs of chew, @gopro , @oakleymotorsports glasses, @botanictonics , flashlight, @benchmadeknifecompany knife, @espinozasleather leather jacket. Who’s ready to hit the road?????
